{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_input_stream_read()"},{"type":"text","text":", this tries to read "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" bytes from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the stream in a blocking fashion. However, rather than reading into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a user-supplied buffer, this will create a new [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes containing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the data that was read. This may be easier to use from language","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"bindings."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readBytes","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"BytesRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8BytesRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If count is zero, returns a zero-length [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes and does nothing. A"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" larger than ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will cause a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, a new [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes is returned. It is not an error if the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"size of this object is not the same as the requested size, as it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file. A zero-length [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returned on end of file (or if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero), but never"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"otherwise.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"was cancelled, the error ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operation was partially finished when the operation was cancelled the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"partial result will be returned, without an error.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On error ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned and ","type":"text"},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is set accordingly."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/pollableinputstreamref\/readbytes(count:cancellable:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentatio